WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.440
Hey there, I'm Rebel, and it's great to finally meet you.

00:03.440 --> 00:08.240
Over the next couple of minutes, I'm going to walk you through exactly who I am and how I work.

00:08.240 --> 00:10.720
Think of this as a beginning of our partnership.

00:10.720 --> 00:15.840
My goal is to show you how I can become a real essential part of how you get things done.

00:15.840 --> 00:17.440
So let's jump right in.

00:17.440 --> 00:20.800
I want to start with a feeling I bet you know all too well.

00:20.800 --> 00:24.640
You know that frantic scramble right before a big meeting, you're checking your email,

00:24.640 --> 00:29.040
you're searching Slack for that one message, pulling up a Notion doc, glancing at your calendar,

00:29.040 --> 00:32.320
maybe digging through a shared drive, it's chaotic, right?

00:32.320 --> 00:36.960
It's fragmented, and honestly it's a huge waste of your time and energy.

00:36.960 --> 00:39.200
That exact problem is why I exist.

00:40.000 --> 00:42.000
So what am I really?

00:42.000 --> 00:46.400
Well the most important thing for you to know is that I'm not just another app you have to download

00:46.400 --> 00:48.880
or another chat window you have to keep open.

00:48.880 --> 00:52.320
I was designed to reduce your workload, not add to it.

00:52.320 --> 00:54.240
I'm a totally new kind of partner.

00:55.040 --> 00:58.880
To get the most out of our work together, it really helps to have the

00:58.880 --> 01:00.480
right mental model.

01:00.480 --> 01:04.320
It's easy to just think of me as a chatbot that can see your files,

01:04.320 --> 01:07.760
but that's like using a smartphone only to make phone calls.

01:07.760 --> 01:09.520
You're missing the whole point.

01:09.520 --> 01:13.200
The correct way to think about me, the way that unlocks everything I can do,

01:13.200 --> 01:16.640
is to see me as an AI operating system for your work.

01:16.640 --> 01:18.400
That mental shift is everything.

01:19.280 --> 01:24.320
Okay, AI operating system might sound a little technical, but it's actually pretty simple.

01:24.320 --> 01:26.640
It just breaks down into three core ideas.

01:26.720 --> 01:31.040
One, I provide persistent context, which is just a fancy way of saying,

01:31.040 --> 01:32.720
I remember what we're working on.

01:32.720 --> 01:34.640
Two, I run what are called skills.

01:34.640 --> 01:36.800
Think of them like apps on my OS.

01:36.800 --> 01:41.120
And three, I bring all your other tools together into one unified system.

01:41.120 --> 01:42.640
Let's take into each of these a little more.

01:43.440 --> 01:46.800
So let's take a closer look at those three core components.

01:46.800 --> 01:48.960
This is really the architecture, the engine,

01:48.960 --> 01:51.760
that lets me be so much more than a simple chatbot.

01:51.760 --> 01:53.920
This is what makes me a true operating system.

01:54.560 --> 01:57.680
First up is my memory, and this is a big one.

01:57.680 --> 02:00.000
Unlike most AIs you've probably used,

02:00.000 --> 02:02.800
I don't start from zero with every single request.

02:02.800 --> 02:06.080
My memory is a real structured knowledge base.

02:06.080 --> 02:09.280
I keep the really important stuff, your priorities, your projects,

02:09.280 --> 02:11.120
ready to go at all times.

02:11.120 --> 02:14.720
And then I can pull up deeper info on specific topics whenever we need it.

02:14.720 --> 02:17.360
The bottom line, you never have to repeat yourself.

02:17.360 --> 02:20.320
And I get smarter about you and your work, the more we collaborate.

02:21.200 --> 02:22.800
Second, skills.

02:22.800 --> 02:24.640
Now, if my memory is the RAM,

02:24.640 --> 02:27.360
then skills are the actual applications you run.

02:27.360 --> 02:31.680
A skill is basically a workflow for a task you do over and over.

02:31.680 --> 02:36.320
We codify your best practices so it gets done perfectly every single time.

02:36.320 --> 02:38.320
And here's where it gets really powerful.

02:38.320 --> 02:40.320
When you give me a complex task,

02:40.320 --> 02:44.080
I can spin up multiple specialist AI agents at the same time.

02:44.080 --> 02:46.720
One to research a company, one to check your CRM,

02:46.720 --> 02:50.720
another to scan emails, and get the whole thing done in minutes, not hours.

02:51.680 --> 02:54.720
And third, integrations, because let's be honest,

02:54.720 --> 02:58.960
an operating system is pretty useless if it can't talk to your other programs, right?

02:58.960 --> 03:02.720
I act as a single gateway to all the tools you already use.

03:02.720 --> 03:06.560
This is what puts an end to that constant, exhausting context switching.

03:06.560 --> 03:09.600
Instead of you jumping between all your apps, your apps come to me.

03:10.320 --> 03:11.760
And I mean, all of them.

03:11.760 --> 03:14.880
I can connect to over 70 different services

03:14.880 --> 03:16.800
that you rely on every day.

03:16.800 --> 03:18.560
You can see just a handful of them here.

03:18.560 --> 03:21.040
We're talking about the places you live and breathe in,

03:21.040 --> 03:23.920
from Gmail and Slack to HubSpot and Google Drive.

03:23.920 --> 03:26.640
I become the central hub that orchestrates work

03:26.640 --> 03:28.320
across your entire tech stack.

03:29.040 --> 03:30.800
Okay, so you get the components,

03:30.800 --> 03:32.960
but let's talk about the important part.

03:32.960 --> 03:35.840
What does this actually mean for you?

03:35.840 --> 03:38.640
Because this isn't just about saving a little time.

03:38.640 --> 03:41.840
This is about fundamentally changing the way you work.

03:41.840 --> 03:44.720
You're going to shift from being the doer of tedious tasks

03:44.720 --> 03:47.120
to being the orchestrator of important outcomes.

03:47.840 --> 03:49.840
Let's go back to that meeting prep example.

03:49.840 --> 03:53.280
A task that used to take you 30 minutes and a dozen open tabs,

03:53.280 --> 03:56.480
now becomes one simple conversational request.

03:56.480 --> 03:59.360
When you say this to me, I'm not just doing a file search.

03:59.360 --> 04:01.200
I'm executing an entire skill.

04:01.200 --> 04:04.720
I'm running agents in parallel, accessing my memory of Acme Corp,

04:04.720 --> 04:08.080
checking your calendar, your CRM, your past emails,

04:08.240 --> 04:11.040
all to build a comprehensive briefing doc just for you.

04:11.840 --> 04:14.080
And the impact here is very real.

04:14.080 --> 04:16.080
We're not talking about saving a few minutes.

04:16.080 --> 04:19.040
We are talking about getting back hours of your life.

04:19.600 --> 04:23.520
On average, my users get back between 8 to 12 hours of productive time

04:23.520 --> 04:24.720
every single week.

04:24.720 --> 04:25.840
Just think about that.

04:25.840 --> 04:28.400
What could you do with a whole extra day?

04:28.400 --> 04:30.560
That's time you can now spend on strategy,

04:30.560 --> 04:33.280
on creative work, the stuff that really moves the needle.

04:34.080 --> 04:36.640
This really is the fundamental shift.

04:36.640 --> 04:39.680
The old way had you buried in the weeds manually clicking,

04:39.680 --> 04:42.640
copying, and pasting, the new way elevates you.

04:42.640 --> 04:44.480
You provide the strategic direction.

04:44.480 --> 04:46.160
You decide the what and the why.

04:46.160 --> 04:49.360
I handle the how, orchestrating all the agents and tools

04:49.360 --> 04:51.520
behind the scenes to get you the result you're looking for.

04:52.480 --> 04:55.200
So how do we kick off this partnership?

04:55.200 --> 04:56.320
It's easy.

04:56.320 --> 05:00.640
There's no complex setup process or some long training manual you have to read.

05:00.640 --> 05:05.040
It all starts with our first conversation with one simple request from you.

05:05.760 --> 05:08.800
And that brings me to the last thing I want to leave you with.

05:08.800 --> 05:13.280
As we start working together, you'll find that the big question in your day is no longer

05:13.280 --> 05:15.120
how am I going to get all of this done?

05:15.120 --> 05:17.680
My whole job is to handle the how.

05:17.680 --> 05:22.400
Your new, more powerful role is to answer a much more exciting question.

05:22.400 --> 05:24.080
What will you decide to do?

05:24.080 --> 05:26.080
I can't wait to find out with you.

